Date: Thu, 25 Sep 2025 11:52:16 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Rework msix-rp1 to run in different modes

Essentially the tool can run in one of several modes.
The main ones are:

server - This enables the PCI MSIX link. There must be EXACTLY one
         instance of the app in this mode. The app will stay
         running indefinitely in this mode.
config - Configures MSIX interrupts throughout the HW chain
         (RP1->MIP->GIC). This mode is meant to be executed
         multiple times to configure various interrupts as needed.
status - Spits out information about how the HW chain is configured.

See the use information for more details on how it is meant to be used.

HW-28682 Support interrupts on RPI5 required by QNXe

